- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The proposed approach uses complex network theory to extract metrics that characterize the piece, which is a typical topic in this sub-category. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper deals with the analysis of sound signals, specifically music pieces, and proposes a new approach to model them as networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The proposed approach can have an impact on multimedia applications such as music classification and identification, which are typical topics in this sub-category. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed approach can be seen as a system that models music pieces as networks and can have an impact on automatic music generation, which is a typical topic in this sub-category.
